  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Takeaways: ",
    "text_level": 1,
    "bbox": [
      752,
      831,
      787,
      847
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "sub_type": "text",
    "list_items": [
      "Permutation module can permute input nodes with little information loss.The largerthe relaxation factorT becomes,the less the information loss is. ",
      "CoCNs learn complementary feature representations under different permutations and require multiple permutations (around 8-16) for sufficient feature learning. ",
      "CoCNs achieve beter performance as the receptive field size increases (bounded by the number of input nodes). ",
      "Both node features and structure features generally contribute to the model prediction. "
    ],
    "bbox": [
      762,
      849,
      980,
      979
    ],
